	<div class="blog-archive-headings-wrapper">
		<div class="blog-archive-month">Week</div>
		<div class="blog-archive-link"><a href="../blog.php">FRC Team 1612 | Blog</a></div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="blog-archive-entries-wrapper">
		<div id="unique-entry-id-16" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Week 5</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, February 13, 2010 Categorized in:<span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-frc.php">FRC</a></span><span class="blog-entry-category"> <a href="category-meetings.php">Meetings</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body">This was a very successful week for us here. We have accomplished everything that was on our list for this week. And if that wasn&rsquo;t enough we also sent off all of our frame material to go get welded. Things are really looking good as we head into the last week of the build season.<br /><br />Today the Robo-Sharks participated in an amazing fundraiser event at our school called Shark-Aid. This event was to raise money and collect non perishable food items to help in the aid of Haiti. Who knew that smashing a pie in someone&rsquo;s face could be so entertaining.<br /><br />~The Robo-Sharks 1612<p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-frc.php" title="FRC" rel="tag">FRC</a>, <a href="tag-meeting.php" title="Meeting" rel="tag">Meeting</a>, <a href="tag-week.php" title="Week" rel="tag">Week</a>, <a href="tag-5.php" title="5" rel="tag">5</a></p></div></div>
<div id="unique-entry-id-14" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Week 4</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, February 06, 2010 Categorized in:<span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-frc.php">FRC</a></span><span class="blog-entry-category"> <a href="category-meetings.php">Meetings</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body">So we have reached the end of the fourth week. There are no major updates for this week just a few minor tweaks that where completed on the robot. The programming team was working hard this week to complete the camera code and test a couple different autonomous situations.<br /><br />This years robot is looking really good we cant wait to see all the teams at regionals this year.<br /><br />~The Robo-Sharks 1612<p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-frc.php" title="FRC" rel="tag">FRC</a>, <a href="tag-meeting.php" title="Meeting" rel="tag">Meeting</a>, <a href="tag-week.php" title="Week" rel="tag">Week</a>, <a href="tag-4.php" title="4" rel="tag">4</a></p></div></div>
<div id="unique-entry-id-13" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Week 3</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, January 30, 2010 Categorized in:<span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-frc.php">FRC</a></span><span class="blog-entry-category"> <a href="category-meetings.php">Meetings</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body">Today we spent all day test our drive system and new control system. It was exciting to see how talented everyone is at driving this year. Here is a quick look at our system for this year, it may look a bit messy at first but it is quite organized if you take a second look.<br /><a href="" rel="self"><img class="imageStyle" alt="IMG_0070" src="img_0070.jpg" width="480" height="360"/></a><br /><br />~The Robo-Sharks 1612<p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-frc.php" title="FRC" rel="tag">FRC</a>, <a href="tag-meeting.php" title="Meeting" rel="tag">Meeting</a>, <a href="tag-week.php" title="Week" rel="tag">Week</a>, <a href="tag-3.php" title="3" rel="tag">3</a></p></div></div>
<div id="unique-entry-id-12" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Week 2</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, January 23, 2010 Categorized in:<span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-frc.php">FRC</a></span><span class="blog-entry-category"> <a href="category-meetings.php">Meetings</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body">This week was very exciting we have finish a few major tasks and the outcome is stunning. We have finished our drive system that we have created. We have developed axel block for our wheels that use gravity to adjust the tension of our chains. While they also tension our chains they also act as a type of suspension system for our robot. These amazing wheel mounts are a miracle and really amazing to see in action. If you are attending the florida regional be sure to stop by our pit and someone will be more then happy to show them to you. We are very proud of our innovative creations that do 2 jobs in one.<br /><br />~The Robo-Sharks 1612<p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-frc.php" title="FRC" rel="tag">FRC</a>, <a href="tag-meeting.php" title="Meeting" rel="tag">Meeting</a>, <a href="tag-week.php" title="Week" rel="tag">Week</a>, <a href="tag-2.php" title="2" rel="tag">2</a></p></div></div>
<div id="unique-entry-id-11" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Week 1</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, January 16, 2010 Categorized in:<span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-frc.php">FRC</a></span><span class="blog-entry-category"> <a href="category-meetings.php">Meetings</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body">Week 1 was very exciting, we have picked a final kicker design that we are going to use. We choice the one that was the most efficient and accurate at scoring. Also we have all agreed upon a general robot design that we would like to prototype. Today we also set many goals as a team as to when we would like to have certain things completed by. Hopefully we can have them done by our expected deadlines.<br /><br />~The Robo-Sharks 1612<p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-frc.php" title="FRC" rel="tag">FRC</a>, <a href="tag-meeting.php" title="Meeting" rel="tag">Meeting</a>, <a href="tag-week.php" title="Week" rel="tag">Week</a>, <a href="tag-1.php" title="1" rel="tag">1</a></p></div></div>
	</div>
	
	 

	
